data.content:
Here are the key modern MSTest patterns:

**1. Async tests** — return `Task`, not `void`:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public async Task FetchAsync_ReturnsContent_OnSuccess()
{
    var handler = new MockHttpMessageHandler("hello", HttpStatusCode.OK);
    var client = new HttpClient(handler);
    var fetcher = new DataFetcher(client);

    string result = await fetcher.FetchAsync("https://example.com");

    Assert.AreEqual("hello", result);
}
```

**2. Timeouts** — use `[Timeout]` or the built-in `TestContext.CancellationTokenSource`:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Timeout(3000)] // fails test if it takes longer than 3s
public async Task FetchAsync_CompletesWithinTimeout()
{
    var handler = new MockHttpMessageHandler("data", HttpStatusCode.OK);
    var client = new HttpClient(handler);
    var fetcher = new DataFetcher(client);

    string result = await fetcher.FetchAsync("https://example.com");

    Assert.AreEqual("data", result);
}
```

**3. Cancellation** — verify your code honors the token:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public async Task FetchAsync_ThrowsOnCancellation()
{
    using var cts = new CancellationTokenSource();
    cts.Cancel(); // pre-cancel

    var handler = new MockHttpMessageHandler("data", HttpStatusCode.OK);
    var client = new HttpClient(handler);
    var fetcher = new DataFetcher(client);

    await Assert.ThrowsExceptionAsync<TaskCanceledException>(
        () => fetcher.FetchAsync("https://example.com", cts.Token));
}
```

**4. Error status codes:**

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public async Task FetchAsync_ThrowsOnServerError()
{
    var handler = new MockHttpMessageHandler("", HttpStatusCode.InternalServerError);
    var client = new HttpClient(handler);
    var fetcher = new DataFetcher(client);

    await Assert.ThrowsExceptionAsync<HttpRequestException>(
        () => fetcher.FetchAsync("https://example.com"));
}
```

**Mock handler** (avoids real HTTP calls):

```csharp
private class MockHttpMessageHandler : HttpMessageHandler
{
    private readonly string _response;
    private readonly HttpStatusCode _statusCode;

    public MockHttpMessageHandler(string response, HttpStatusCode statusCode)
    {
        _response = response;
        _statusCode = statusCode;
    }

    protected override async Task<HttpResponseMessage> SendAsync(
        HttpRequestMessage request, CancellationToken cancellationToken)
    {
        cancellationToken.ThrowIfCancellationRequested();
        await Task.Yield(); // simulate async work
        return new HttpResponseMessage(_statusCode)
        {
            Content = new StringContent(_response)
        };
    }
}
```

**Key takeaways:**
- Always use `async Task` (never `async void`) for test methods
- `[Timeout(ms)]` auto-fails slow tests — good for CI guardrails
- Test cancellation by pre-canceling a `CancellationTokenSource`
- Mock `HttpMessageHandler` (not `HttpClient`) to control responses
- Use `Assert.ThrowsExceptionAsync<T>` for async exception assertions
